/* gamedata-w3-equinox.mjs — Equinox (Dream/rift-gated, late-game system) tables, extracted
 * verbatim from N.js. GENERATED by a one-off extraction script (scratchpad, not committed);
 * refresh after a major patch.
 *
 * Internal naming: the client calls this system "Dream"/"Dreamstuff" everywhere, NOT "Equinox" —
 * `_customBlock_Dreamstuff` (N.js:17906), game attribute `Dream` (24-element array per save,
 * `Dream[0]`=current bar charge, `Dream[1]`=unused/spare, `Dream[2]`=clouds-owned counter,
 * `Dream[2+i]`=level of EQUINOX_UPGRADES[i] for i=0..13), and `WeeklyBoss.h["d_"+idx]` tracks
 * challenge `idx`'s progress (-1 once claimed/completed, else the running counter — see "CLOUD
 * BONUS" below). Only the UI-facing strings say "Equinox"/"Dream cloud".
 *
 * SOURCES:
 *   EQUINOX_UPGRADES   na.DreamUpg()      (N.js:23801-23803) — 14 rows, registered into
 *                       CustomLists.DreamUpg at N.js:30247/34310.
 *   EQUINOX_CHALLENGES na.DreamChallenge() (N.js:23782-23800) — 77 rows, registered into
 *                       CustomLists.DreamChallenge at the same two call sites.
 * Extracted with a scratchpad Node script that sliced the `na.X=function(){return[...]}` array
 * literal directly out of N.js text and evaluated it (both are pure string/number literals, no
 * function calls inside) — safer and more exhaustive than manual transcription for a 77-row table.
 *
 * CROSS-CHECK vs idleon-toolbox/data/website-data.json (`equinoxUpgrades`, `equinoxChallenges`):
 * 0 mismatches across all 14 upgrade rows (name/description/maxLevel/bonus) and all 77 challenge
 * rows (label/goal/reward). Toolbox's own parser (idleon-toolbox/parsers/world-3/equinox.ts) was
 * also read for context (not as a data source) — its `getEquinox`/`getEquinoxBonus` logic matches
 * every formula transcribed below line-for-line, which independently corroborates the N.js read.
 *
 * ============================================================================================
 * EQUINOX_UPGRADES row shape: [name, description, baseMaxLv, perLevelBonus] (desc_line1-style
 * verbatim strings, `_`-separated like every other W1-3 gamedata file in this repo).
 *   - `description` embeds the game's OWN tooltip template markers:
 *       "{" immediately followed by a number (e.g. "{9%") is NOT a placeholder — it's a literal
 *       fragment of the tooltip text (a stylized bullet/highlight glyph the renderer draws before
 *       the per-level stat clause). Only "}" is a live substitution token.
 *       Render logic (N.js:18792-18793, function unnamed — inline in the Equinox tooltip draw
 *       block, reachable via `_customEvent_dreamStuffs`):
 *         text = EQUINOX_UPGRADES[i].name + "_@___@_" + EQUINOX_UPGRADES[i].description
 *         if "}" in text:
 *           text = text.replace("}", String(Dream[2+i] * EQUINOX_UPGRADES[i].perLevelBonus))
 *       i.e. the upgrade's CURRENT TOTAL BONUS is simply `level * perLevelBonus` — no decay/add
 *       ArbitraryCode5Inputs curve is involved here (unlike stamps/cards/post-office boxes; this
 *       system uses flat linear scaling per level, confirmed by toolbox's
 *       `bonus * dream[index]` in parseEquinoxUpgrades, matching exactly).
 *   - `baseMaxLv` is the level cap BEFORE per-upgrade achievement/cloud bonuses (see MAX-LV
 *     BONUSES below) are added; UI shows "Lv. X / maxLv" using the post-bonus total.
 *   - Row 13 ("Hmm...", desc "Huh...", baseMaxLv 2, perLevelBonus "Filler") is a genuine joke/
 *     placeholder row in the client's own table — verbatim, not an extraction artifact. Its
 *     `perLevelBonus` field literally contains the string "Filler" (not a number) in N.js;
 *     represented as `null` below. Toolbox encodes it as `bonus: null` too (independent match).
 *
 * MAX-LV BONUSES (N.js:17908-17913, `_customBlock_Dreamstuff("UpgMaxLV", i)`) — per-upgrade-index
 * switch adding challenge-completion and other account bonuses on top of baseMaxLv. Transcribed
 * verbatim; `CloudBonus(idx)` = 1 if EQUINOX_CHALLENGES[idx] has been completed/claimed, else 0
 * (see CLOUD BONUS below). `Summoning("WinBonus",24,0)` and `GamingStatType("SuperBitType",35,0)`
 * are account-wide bonus sources outside this file's scope (cite only, don't extract):
 *   UpgMaxLV(i) =
 *     i==3  -> round(baseMaxLv[3]  + 3*CloudBonus(6)  + 4*CloudBonus(15))
 *     i==4  -> round(baseMaxLv[4]  + WinBonus24 + 10*SuperBitType35
 *                     + 5*CloudBonus(12) + 10*CloudBonus(18) + 10*CloudBonus(34) + 10*CloudBonus(39))
 *     i==5  -> round(baseMaxLv[5]  + WinBonus24 + 10*SuperBitType35 + 6*CloudBonus(32))
 *     i==8  -> round(baseMaxLv[8]  + WinBonus24 + 10*SuperBitType35
 *                     + 5*CloudBonus(21) + 10*CloudBonus(26))
 *     i==9  -> round(baseMaxLv[9]  + WinBonus24 + 10*SuperBitType35 + 4*CloudBonus(25))
 *     i==10 -> round(baseMaxLv[10] + WinBonus24 + 10*SuperBitType35 + 4*CloudBonus(30))
 *     i==11 -> round(baseMaxLv[11] + WinBonus24 + 10*SuperBitType35 + 15*CloudBonus(35))
 *     i==7  -> round(baseMaxLv[7]  + WinBonus24 + 10*SuperBitType35)
 *     i==12 -> round(baseMaxLv[12] + WinBonus24
 *                     + 5*CloudBonus(37) + 5*CloudBonus(42) + 5*CloudBonus(43) + 5*CloudBonus(47)
 *                     + 5*CloudBonus(50) + 5*CloudBonus(55) + 6*CloudBonus(58) + 6*CloudBonus(61)
 *                     + 7*CloudBonus(64) + 8*CloudBonus(75))
 *     else  -> round(baseMaxLv[i])                    // i.e. 0,1,2,6,13: no bonus sources
 *
 * CLOUD BONUS / challenge-completion flag (N.js:17906, `CloudBonus` case):
 *   CloudBonus(idx) = (WeeklyBoss.h["d_"+idx] === -1) ? 1 : 0
 * A challenge's tracker is set to -1 exactly once, at claim time (N.js:18778:
 *   `WeeklyBoss.h["d_"+challengeIdx] = -1` fires when its progress counter reaches
 *   EQUINOX_CHALLENGES[challengeIdx].goal and the reward is collected). So CloudBonus(idx)==1
 *   means "challenge idx has been completed/claimed", NOT "cloud idx is currently visible" —
 *   confirmed by toolbox's `getCloudBonus` doing the identical `current === -1` check.
 *
 * CLOUD VISIBILITY / "clouds owned" (N.js:17907, 17913-17914):
 *   CloudsOwned      = round(min(5, Dream[2]))                 // max 5 clouds visible at once
 *   UpgUnlocked       = round(1 + CloudBonus(0)+CloudBonus(2)+CloudBonus(5)+CloudBonus(7)
 *                              +CloudBonus(10)+CloudBonus(13)+CloudBonus(17)+CloudBonus(20)
 *                              +CloudBonus(23)+CloudBonus(28)+CloudBonus(31)+CloudBonus(36))
 *                       // number of EQUINOX_UPGRADES rows unlocked so far — gated behind
 *                       // completing the "Unlock_next_Equinox_upgrade"-reward challenges above
 *   CloudsTask(cloudSlot) — builds DreamDL = [idx for idx in 0..76 if challenge idx not -1
 *     (i.e. not yet claimed)], then returns DreamDL[cloudSlot] UNLESS that challenge index is
 *     >=36 AND ResearchStuff("Grid_Bonus",86,1) < 1, in which case -1 (challenges 36-76 require a
 *     Research Grid unlock — cite only, Research is out of this file's scope).
 *
 * BAR-FILL REQUIREMENT ("charge required", N.js:17914):
 *   totalUpgradeLv = sum(Dream[2] .. Dream[15])                // sum of all 14 upgrade levels
 *   BarFillReq = round((120 + 40*totalUpgradeLv) * pow(1.02, totalUpgradeLv))
 *
 * BAR-FILL RATE ("charge rate", N.js:17915-17918) — matches research's "~15+ bonus sources +
 * Clouds (additive + 5 mul thresholds)" note exactly; transcribed verbatim, NOT re-derived (every
 * `X(...)` call below is an account-wide bonus source owned by other W1-6 gamedata/recipe files —
 * cite only):
 *   base = 60
 *     * (1 + min(0.5, 0.5*BundlesReceived.bun_q))               // bundle purchase, capped +50%
 *     * (1 + Summoning("VotingBonusz",32,0)/100)
 *     * (1 + ResearchStuff("Grid_Bonus",86,0)/100)
 *     * (1 + Thingies("LoreEpiBon",8,0)/100)
 *     * (1 + Companions(15))
 *     * (1 + Holes("CosmoBonusQTY",2,5)/100)
 *     * (1 + 0.5*Summoning("EventShopOwned",3,0))
 *     * (1 + OptionsListAccount[320]/10)                        // penguin-pal bonus slot
 *     * (1 + ArcaneType("ArcaneUpgBonus",37,0)/100)
 *     * (1 + 3*CloudBonus(45)/100)                               // <- "5 mul thresholds" start
 *     * (1 + 5*CloudBonus(49)/100)
 *     * (1 + 6*CloudBonus(52)/100)
 *     * (1 + 7*CloudBonus(59)/100)
 *     * (1 + 7*CloudBonus(67)/100)                               // <- "5 mul thresholds" end
 *     * (1 + (AlchVials.EqBar                                    // <- "additive" cloud stack:
 *             + 10*CloudBonus(3)  + 15*CloudBonus(9)  + 20*CloudBonus(14) + 25*CloudBonus(19)
 *             + 30*CloudBonus(22) + 35*CloudBonus(24) + 40*CloudBonus(29) + ArcadeBonus(41)
 *             + Thingies("EmperorBon",5,0)
 *             + 60*CloudBonus(38) + 65*CloudBonus(40) + 75*CloudBonus(44) + 90*CloudBonus(46)
 *             + 100*CloudBonus(48) + 120*CloudBonus(51) + 150*CloudBonus(54) + 160*CloudBonus(56)
 *             + 170*CloudBonus(57) + 185*CloudBonus(60) + 190*CloudBonus(62) + 195*CloudBonus(63)
 *             + 200*CloudBonus(65) + 220*CloudBonus(68) + 250*CloudBonus(74)) / 100)
 *   BarFillRate = round(base)
 *   IsBarFULL   = Dream[0] >= ceil(BarFillReq) ? 1 : 0
 * NOTE: there is NO separate "N clouds unlocked -> multiplier" breakpoint TABLE in the data —
 * research's "5 mul thresholds" and "additive" clouds are each individual CloudBonus(challengeIdx)
 * terms hard-coded directly into this one formula (i.e. the "cloud mechanic" IS this challenge-
 * completion-flag stack, not a separate data structure). Nothing further to extract as a table.
 *
 * CloudX/CloudY (N.js:17906) are pure UI pixel-layout helpers for drawing cloud icons on the
 * Equinox screen — not extracted, no gameplay-numeric value:
 *   CloudX(b) = 43 + (152*b + 13*floor(b/2));  CloudY(b) = 14 + 105*(b - 2*floor(b/2))
 * AllShimmerBonuses (N.js:17906) is an unrelated sailing-artifact multiplier reused inside this
 * dispatcher's namespace by convention, not an Equinox-specific value — not extracted here.
 * ============================================================================================
 */

